 nontrivial way. All four new predictors are found\nuseful for inclusion in an automated flare forecasting facility, such as the\nFlare Likelihood and Region Eruption Forecasting (FLARECAST), but their\nutility, among others, will ultimately be determined by the validation effort\nunderway in the framework of the FLARECAST project.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jul 2018 12:06:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-18"}
